WEBVTT

00:01:29.500 --> 00:01:34.900
[Our Dazzling Days]

00:01:35.490 --> 00:01:37.700
[Episode 27]

00:01:40.590 --> 00:01:41.250
Light it up!

00:01:41.479 --> 00:01:43.120
-Hurry up.
-Dongdong, what are you doing?

00:01:43.120 --> 00:01:43.870
Come on!

00:01:43.870 --> 00:01:45.150
Light it up!

00:01:45.150 --> 00:01:47.080
-Light it up!
-Dongdong. Light it.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:55.660
We're open!

00:01:55.950 --> 00:01:56.610
We're open!

00:01:57.509 --> 00:01:58.479
Stop twisting it, Xiaoman.

00:01:58.479 --> 00:01:59.229
One more!

00:01:59.229 --> 00:01:59.920
Let them pop.

00:01:59.920 --> 00:02:02.320
-I triggered it.
-Of course I triggered it.

00:02:33.770 --> 00:02:34.600
Mr. Zhao.

00:02:34.840 --> 00:02:35.710
Are you done packing

00:02:35.710 --> 00:02:36.710
and ready to move?

00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:39.280
You've got a lot of stuff.

00:02:39.710 --> 00:02:41.190
Where did you find this moving company?

00:02:41.190 --> 00:02:42.320
They seem reliable.

00:02:42.800 --> 00:02:43.310
Not bad, huh?

00:02:43.310 --> 00:02:44.370
Yeah, pretty good.

00:02:44.560 --> 00:02:45.630
Aside from everything else,

00:02:45.630 --> 00:02:46.829
just look at my books.

00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:49.520
They took photos before moving them.

00:02:49.870 --> 00:02:51.079
When we get to the new house,

00:02:51.079 --> 00:02:53.470
they'll be in the exact same order.

00:02:53.870 --> 00:02:55.190
That saves me so much trouble.

00:02:55.190 --> 00:02:56.000
Yeah.

00:02:56.530 --> 00:02:57.570
Manyi Moving?

00:02:59.000 --> 00:02:59.960
What a name.

00:03:00.590 --> 00:03:01.630
So fancy.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:03.080
Where are they?

00:03:03.640 --> 00:03:04.270
Okay.

00:03:08.680 --> 00:03:09.430
Young men.

00:03:09.680 --> 00:03:11.970
You guys are pretty reliable and meticulous.

00:03:11.970 --> 00:03:12.560
Thank you.

00:03:12.560 --> 00:03:14.560
Do you have a business card that you can give me?

00:03:14.560 --> 00:03:15.240
Yes, we do.

00:03:15.240 --> 00:03:15.630
We do.

00:03:16.200 --> 00:03:16.930
Be careful.

00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:20.079
My house is almost done being decorated.

00:03:20.079 --> 00:03:21.140
We're getting ready to move.

00:03:21.140 --> 00:03:22.070
Here's the card.

00:03:23.150 --> 00:03:24.630
That's another moving company.

00:03:24.630 --> 00:03:25.680
Isn't that stealing our business?

00:03:25.680 --> 00:03:26.840
I don't need you to tell me that.

00:03:26.840 --> 00:03:27.930
Piss off and get back to work.

00:03:27.930 --> 00:03:28.460
Get lost!

00:03:30.030 --> 00:03:31.050
Yan, you're back?

00:03:32.460 --> 00:03:35.130
So many people at the plant
say hello to me now.

00:03:36.030 --> 00:03:37.800
But I always forget who they are.

00:03:37.800 --> 00:03:38.710
It's fine.

00:03:39.290 --> 00:03:41.150
They must be your old colleagues.

00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:49.590
What a lousy move.

00:03:51.770 --> 00:03:53.430
Mr. Yan, when did you get back?

00:03:54.920 --> 00:03:56.990
Lousy move? You play then.

00:03:57.960 --> 00:03:58.890
I'm not playing.

00:03:58.910 --> 00:04:00.430
Then don't yap.

00:04:01.060 --> 00:04:02.760
A true gentleman
watches chess games in silence.

00:04:02.760 --> 00:04:04.710
-True gentleman?
-You're no gentleman.

00:04:04.710 --> 00:04:05.710
Truth gentleman?

00:04:06.630 --> 00:04:07.910
With your skills?

00:04:08.190 --> 00:04:10.470
Not to mention you. You all know, right?

00:04:10.470 --> 00:04:11.030
We do.

00:04:11.080 --> 00:04:13.310
Not just in our plant—
even including the main plant...

00:04:13.310 --> 00:04:13.680
Right.

00:04:13.680 --> 00:04:14.590
No one can beat me.

00:04:14.590 --> 00:04:15.030
You.

00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:16.800
Yes.

00:04:16.870 --> 00:04:18.390
Only your senior

00:04:18.390 --> 00:04:20.070
can barely tie with me.

00:04:20.070 --> 00:04:20.680
Yan.

00:04:20.680 --> 00:04:22.680
Yan Wenyuan, what do you mean?

00:04:22.800 --> 00:04:23.800
Why did you bring up my senior?

00:04:23.800 --> 00:04:25.310
What's wrong with bringing him up?

00:04:25.310 --> 00:04:26.680
He plays better than you.

00:04:26.680 --> 00:04:27.480
Then play me. Come on.

00:04:27.480 --> 00:04:28.560
Play you?

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:29.560
I won't play you.

00:04:29.720 --> 00:04:31.070
You're not good enough.

00:04:31.160 --> 00:04:32.560
Why would I play with you?

00:04:32.560 --> 00:04:33.830
With your skills...

00:04:33.830 --> 00:04:34.360
Let's go.

00:04:34.360 --> 00:04:36.070
I won't give you the chance.

00:04:36.360 --> 00:04:37.760
He dares to challenge me?

00:04:37.870 --> 00:04:39.480
Why would I play him?

00:04:39.560 --> 00:04:41.190
Don't you know your own level?

00:04:41.190 --> 00:04:43.159
Enough, Dad. I'm hungry.

00:04:43.240 --> 00:04:44.510
-I'm hungry. Time to eat.
-I won't give him the chance.

00:04:44.510 --> 00:04:45.510
Sorry about that.

00:04:45.570 --> 00:04:47.330
Come on. Sit.

00:04:57.830 --> 00:04:58.760
Mr. Xia,

00:04:58.790 --> 00:05:00.720
this plan has been revised back and forth,

00:05:00.720 --> 00:05:02.920
but there haven't been any big changes.

00:05:03.190 --> 00:05:04.190
Here's the thing.

00:05:04.830 --> 00:05:07.920
I've asked the company
for the greatest sincerity.

00:05:08.360 --> 00:05:10.820
I don't think others
can give you this price.

00:05:12.680 --> 00:05:13.510
Now,

00:05:13.670 --> 00:05:15.340
there is a boss from the south.

00:05:15.430 --> 00:05:18.040
He always offers
just a little more than you

00:05:18.040 --> 00:05:19.240
to make a deal with me.

00:05:20.720 --> 00:05:22.240
I don't quite understand what you mean.

00:05:22.240 --> 00:05:23.600
I've said this before.

00:05:24.190 --> 00:05:26.510
The Provincial State-owned
Assets Commission has made it clear.

00:05:26.510 --> 00:05:27.870
Whoever offers better terms

00:05:27.870 --> 00:05:28.730
will be chosen.

00:05:29.720 --> 00:05:31.600
How could an outsider know
my reserve price?

00:05:31.600 --> 00:05:32.600
Unless someone helped him.

00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:33.190
Who?

00:05:34.560 --> 00:05:35.480
Me?

00:05:37.190 --> 00:05:38.040
Xia Lei, if you're going to

00:05:38.040 --> 00:05:39.680
speak to me with that attitude,

00:05:39.680 --> 00:05:41.540
I don't think we need to continue.

00:05:42.040 --> 00:05:43.800
Mr. Song, don't get upset. It's just...

00:05:43.800 --> 00:05:44.950
Here's the thing.

00:05:45.120 --> 00:05:47.050
Every time, I come with sincerity.

00:05:47.680 --> 00:05:49.070
Lately, you've been

00:05:49.070 --> 00:05:50.950
increasing the price.

00:05:50.950 --> 00:05:52.510
I'm not sure what to make of it.

00:05:52.510 --> 00:05:54.750
How did it become so much all of a sudden?

00:05:54.750 --> 00:05:56.870
Right? If you want that much money...

00:05:56.870 --> 00:05:57.510
then don't...

00:05:57.510 --> 00:05:58.570
Alright, alright.

00:05:59.310 --> 00:06:00.170
How about this?

00:06:01.240 --> 00:06:02.300
I have things to do.

00:06:02.540 --> 00:06:04.690
Mr. Xia, let's call it a day.

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:05.680
Okay?

00:06:08.680 --> 00:06:09.880
As for this proposal,

00:06:10.430 --> 00:06:11.760
take another look at it.

00:06:14.830 --> 00:06:16.190
Okay, I'll revise it.

00:06:16.210 --> 00:06:18.160
I'll let you know as soon as I finish.

00:06:18.160 --> 00:06:18.770
Okay.

00:06:29.240 --> 00:06:30.770
You guys talked for so long.

00:06:33.240 --> 00:06:34.570
What are you doing here?

00:06:35.630 --> 00:06:37.159
Doing business, of course.

00:06:38.920 --> 00:06:40.250
How do you know my price?

00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:46.270
When did you get in touch with Kong Peng?

00:06:48.750 --> 00:06:50.340
I haven't seen you for a while.

00:06:50.340 --> 00:06:51.740
You've really improved.

00:06:52.040 --> 00:06:53.510
Since you know everything,

00:06:53.510 --> 00:06:54.970
I'll be straight with you.

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:55.800
You withdraw,

00:06:56.190 --> 00:06:57.460
and I'll make it worth your while.

00:06:57.460 --> 00:06:58.460
What do you think?

00:07:02.630 --> 00:07:03.690
Fan Weijie, why...

00:07:03.750 --> 00:07:05.550
Why should I cooperate with you?

00:07:06.170 --> 00:07:07.930
I just praised you for nothing.

00:07:09.270 --> 00:07:10.080
Lei,

00:07:10.640 --> 00:07:11.630
do you really think Kong Peng

00:07:11.630 --> 00:07:13.290
will let you secure this deal?

00:07:13.920 --> 00:07:15.000
What I'm offering Kong Peng,

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:16.310
Fenlier can't afford.

00:07:17.390 --> 00:07:19.520
Besides, Fenlier doesn't do charity.

00:07:19.700 --> 00:07:20.410
After all,

00:07:20.660 --> 00:07:23.310
Kong Peng never intended
to revitalize Factory No. 3.

00:07:23.310 --> 00:07:24.560
You're just a cannon foil

00:07:24.560 --> 00:07:26.160
to explore the bottom price.

00:07:27.390 --> 00:07:29.450
Do you remember Director Li's plant?

00:07:29.920 --> 00:07:31.580
You probably don't know this—

00:07:31.710 --> 00:07:33.420
Director Li
went to Fenlier to make a scene.

00:07:33.420 --> 00:07:34.630
Liar! Get out here!

00:07:34.830 --> 00:07:35.430
Liar!

00:07:35.680 --> 00:07:38.000
Revitalize? That's just a lie.

00:07:38.480 --> 00:07:40.680
It's actually a purge
to clear out old workers,

00:07:40.680 --> 00:07:43.110
to turn this plant
into a contract manufacturer for Fenlier.

00:07:43.110 --> 00:07:44.630
It's the same for your Factory No. 3.

00:07:44.630 --> 00:07:46.490
They want capacity and channels,

00:07:46.510 --> 00:07:47.870
not the old employees

00:07:47.870 --> 00:07:49.870
you've been fighting so hard to protect.

00:07:49.870 --> 00:07:51.130
Instead of competing,

00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:53.040
we might as well cooperate.

00:07:53.040 --> 00:07:55.700
Do you really think
you have a future at Fenlier?

00:07:57.830 --> 00:08:00.040
You should worry about yourself first.

00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:04.270
Pawns eventually get sacrificed.

00:08:04.270 --> 00:08:05.470
You know that, right?

00:08:06.360 --> 00:08:07.120
Thanks.

00:08:10.160 --> 00:08:11.000
It's time.

00:08:11.870 --> 00:08:13.530
It's my turn to talk to him now.

00:08:23.560 --> 00:08:25.160
I guess you've run into some trouble.

00:08:25.160 --> 00:08:26.680
I just met Fan Weijie.

00:08:28.230 --> 00:08:30.240
He also wants to acquire Factory No. 3.

00:08:30.240 --> 00:08:31.040
What's more interesting is

00:08:31.040 --> 00:08:33.020
that his price
is always slightly higher than mine,

00:08:33.020 --> 00:08:34.940
and this is related to Kong Peng.

00:08:35.559 --> 00:08:38.020
There's nothing we can do
without evidence.

00:08:39.909 --> 00:08:41.390
Although I thought at first

00:08:41.390 --> 00:08:43.510
Kong Peng wouldn't let you off so easily,

00:08:43.510 --> 00:08:45.630
but since he can cooperate
with Fan Weijie,

00:08:45.630 --> 00:08:47.720
the two of them
must have reached some agreement.

00:08:47.720 --> 00:08:49.780
Kong Peng really is quite something.

00:08:50.360 --> 00:08:52.750
He wants to get rid of me
as the thorn in his side,

00:08:52.750 --> 00:08:55.320
yet at the same time, he wants to make
Factory No. 3 bigger and stronger

00:08:55.320 --> 00:08:56.200
so that he can swallow it.

00:08:56.200 --> 00:08:57.000
So,

00:08:57.360 --> 00:08:58.970
from the start,
this project has been about

00:08:58.970 --> 00:09:00.750
each side getting what they need.

00:09:00.750 --> 00:09:02.030
Business is like a battlefield.

00:09:02.030 --> 00:09:03.550
Don't let your feelings get in the way.

00:09:03.550 --> 00:09:04.320
Stay sharp.

00:09:16.230 --> 00:09:17.360
Why is he here?

00:09:17.840 --> 00:09:18.510
Be careful.

00:09:18.510 --> 00:09:19.030
Unbuckle it!

00:09:19.030 --> 00:09:19.750
Don't scratch or bump it.

00:09:19.750 --> 00:09:21.270
-Unbuckle it!
-Don't worry, it's safe.

00:09:21.270 --> 00:09:22.470
What's going on here?

00:09:25.270 --> 00:09:25.790
Liu.

00:09:27.150 --> 00:09:29.440
Wh-What's going on?

00:09:30.510 --> 00:09:31.840
They came to me.

00:09:32.510 --> 00:09:34.200
Their price is half of yours.

00:09:34.750 --> 00:09:37.080
Xiaoman, if you give me their price,

00:09:37.240 --> 00:09:38.640
I'll still hire you guys.

00:09:39.390 --> 00:09:40.200
Come on, sir.

00:09:40.200 --> 00:09:41.750
We agreed on this price.

00:09:41.750 --> 00:09:42.840
You can't go back on your word.

00:09:42.840 --> 00:09:43.360
Come on!

00:09:43.700 --> 00:09:45.030
He's not going back on his word.

00:09:45.030 --> 00:09:46.630
He's reasoning with you politely.

00:09:46.630 --> 00:09:47.600
Why are you

00:09:47.600 --> 00:09:48.670
accusing him of breaking his word?

00:09:48.670 --> 00:09:49.270
Besides,

00:09:49.270 --> 00:09:51.550
is it wrong for me
to save money for the customer?

00:09:51.550 --> 00:09:52.870
Who wants to waste money?

00:09:52.870 --> 00:09:53.750
Only a fool would do that.

00:09:53.750 --> 00:09:54.240
Right, Liu?

00:09:54.240 --> 00:09:56.910
Bro, is that even a normal price?

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:59.800
You're openly stealing our business,
aren't you?

00:10:01.440 --> 00:10:02.200
Liu.

00:10:03.130 --> 00:10:04.320
We had a deal.

00:10:04.320 --> 00:10:05.550
We've canceled all other work today.

00:10:05.550 --> 00:10:06.720
Stop the nonsense.

00:10:06.720 --> 00:10:07.120
I really...

00:10:07.120 --> 00:10:08.180
Get lost! Get lost!

00:10:08.240 --> 00:10:09.480
Who do you think
you're telling to get lost?

00:10:09.480 --> 00:10:11.140
Are you looking for a beating?

00:10:11.720 --> 00:10:12.390
Hurry up!

00:10:12.390 --> 00:10:13.360
Are you just going to let this go?

00:10:13.360 --> 00:10:14.360
With these thugs here?

00:10:14.360 --> 00:10:15.670
Don't cause trouble when we're out.

00:10:15.670 --> 00:10:18.120
Their price is cheaper. What can we do?

00:10:18.360 --> 00:10:19.840
Come on. Let me tell you, Xiaoman.

00:10:19.840 --> 00:10:21.440
Do you know why I'm so serious with them?

00:10:21.440 --> 00:10:23.000
I think there should be
a limit to everything.

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:23.600
Do you understand?

00:10:23.600 --> 00:10:24.730
What are they doing?

00:10:24.790 --> 00:10:26.080
We turned down all our other work.

00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:27.120
And they pulled this stunt.

00:10:27.120 --> 00:10:28.510
We kept our word!

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:29.910
Why haven't you started working?

00:10:29.910 --> 00:10:31.000
Isn't this a big job?

00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:32.750
Da, don't be angry.
Now we don't need to do anything.

00:10:32.750 --> 00:10:33.600
Just think of it as a day off.

00:10:33.600 --> 00:10:35.240
I'll buy us some beer tonight.
Let's have a drink.

00:10:35.240 --> 00:10:35.670
No.

00:10:35.790 --> 00:10:36.390
It's just...

00:10:36.390 --> 00:10:38.270
I really can't swallow this insult,
you know?

00:10:38.270 --> 00:10:40.200
He's obviously trying to screw us over.

00:10:40.200 --> 00:10:41.730
He thinks we're pushovers.

00:10:42.680 --> 00:10:43.680
What's wrong, Da?

00:10:44.600 --> 00:10:46.460
You can't control your temper again?

00:10:46.460 --> 00:10:48.200
You've had enough of the good life

00:10:48.200 --> 00:10:49.110
and it's time for prison now, huh?

00:10:49.110 --> 00:10:50.770
What's with all the fighting?

00:10:51.440 --> 00:10:53.040
It's obvious what happened.

00:10:53.550 --> 00:10:54.670
Curb your temper.

00:10:55.600 --> 00:10:57.270
Listen to me.

00:10:57.790 --> 00:10:59.120
Harmony brings wealth.

00:11:02.630 --> 00:11:03.510
Oh my god!

00:11:03.790 --> 00:11:05.360
Ding! Ding!

00:11:05.360 --> 00:11:07.390
Ding! It's smudged! Ding!

00:11:07.390 --> 00:11:08.550
What is smudged?

00:11:08.550 --> 00:11:09.240
What?

00:11:09.240 --> 00:11:11.750
The glass. The glass is smudged.

00:11:14.390 --> 00:11:15.150
Who did this?

00:11:15.150 --> 00:11:15.960
Who did this?

00:11:15.960 --> 00:11:16.750
Did you see who did this?

00:11:16.750 --> 00:11:17.750
I didn't see anyone.

00:11:17.750 --> 00:11:19.120
Which bastard did this?

00:11:19.910 --> 00:11:21.170
Don't let me catch him!

00:11:21.270 --> 00:11:22.440
I'll kill him!

00:11:22.670 --> 00:11:24.800
That's so mean! Why would they do this?

00:11:25.200 --> 00:11:26.270
That's so shady!

00:11:27.080 --> 00:11:28.480
Xiaoman, let me tell you,

00:11:28.510 --> 00:11:29.200
if this were a few years ago,

00:11:29.200 --> 00:11:31.200
I would have flattened their house!

00:11:31.910 --> 00:11:32.970
Is it the black car?

00:11:33.080 --> 00:11:34.480
Don't worry. I asked around.

00:11:34.480 --> 00:11:35.210
Are you sure?

00:11:35.220 --> 00:11:35.820
Yes.

00:11:35.840 --> 00:11:36.890
Wait.

00:11:40.210 --> 00:11:40.810
Let's go.

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:45.630
Hello?

00:11:46.510 --> 00:11:47.570
Wait for me at home.

00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:50.120
Didn't I tell you? I've already eaten.

00:11:50.120 --> 00:11:51.980
Why did you bother cooking for me?

00:11:52.750 --> 00:11:54.150
What's the use of getting angry?

00:11:54.150 --> 00:11:55.230
Wait for me a bit longer.

00:11:55.230 --> 00:11:57.160
I'll be back in a while. Okay.

00:12:19.950 --> 00:12:20.790
No need to come in.

00:12:20.790 --> 00:12:21.390
Alright.

00:12:30.560 --> 00:12:31.640
Jinlong, what are you doing?

00:12:31.640 --> 00:12:33.100
Mr. Ding, stay out of this.

00:12:33.570 --> 00:12:34.570
Where is your dad?

00:12:34.890 --> 00:12:35.750
Zhang Xiaoman!

00:12:35.750 --> 00:12:37.610
Who are you? Why are you shouting?

00:12:39.050 --> 00:12:39.850
Get down here!

00:12:40.270 --> 00:12:41.120
Wh-what the hell are you doing?

00:12:41.120 --> 00:12:42.270
-Who is it?
-Why are you shouting?

00:12:42.270 --> 00:12:42.800
Jinlong.

00:12:44.160 --> 00:12:46.080
Jinlong? What do you want?

00:12:46.390 --> 00:12:48.520
What do I want? You think you're tough?

00:12:48.630 --> 00:12:51.630
Do you know how many days
I spent puking because of you?

00:12:51.870 --> 00:12:53.030
Let me tell you.

00:12:53.120 --> 00:12:53.790
If you know what's good for you,

00:12:53.790 --> 00:12:55.600
take down this damn sign right now.

00:12:55.600 --> 00:12:57.750
Or else I'll kill you.

00:12:57.790 --> 00:12:59.790
Enough.
Can't you pick up some good habits?

00:12:59.790 --> 00:13:00.600
Always talking about killing.

00:13:00.600 --> 00:13:02.120
Let me see
how many people you've actually killed.

00:13:02.120 --> 00:13:03.320
This is a society ruled by law.

00:13:03.320 --> 00:13:04.480
Fair business competition

00:13:04.480 --> 00:13:05.750
is normal, isn't it?

00:13:06.600 --> 00:13:08.000
Let me tell you something.

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:10.030
This is between him and me.

00:13:10.200 --> 00:13:12.000
If any of you dares to interfere,

00:13:12.390 --> 00:13:13.670
I'll kill them.

00:13:14.080 --> 00:13:14.960
Who do you think you're pointing at?

00:13:14.960 --> 00:13:17.150
Alright, that's enough.

00:13:17.250 --> 00:13:19.600
Look at how old you are.
Always talking about killing people.

00:13:19.600 --> 00:13:21.790
I'll do as you say.
Let's fight one-on-one.

00:13:21.790 --> 00:13:22.480
One-on-one?

00:13:22.480 --> 00:13:23.600
Who's going to fight you?

00:13:23.600 --> 00:13:24.270
Look at you.

00:13:25.470 --> 00:13:27.510
Xiaoman,
don't start a fight. Listen to me.

00:13:27.510 --> 00:13:28.840
No one calls the police!

00:13:29.320 --> 00:13:30.010
Okay.

00:13:30.510 --> 00:13:34.550
Let's see if your fist is harder
than my face.

00:13:36.150 --> 00:13:37.030
Let's do this.

00:13:37.240 --> 00:13:37.750
Come on.

00:13:37.750 --> 00:13:38.950
-Let's do this.
-I...

00:13:40.390 --> 00:13:41.360
You never stop!

00:13:41.790 --> 00:13:43.550
You're a grown man,
yet you don't know when to stop.

00:13:43.550 --> 00:13:44.390
Let go of me!

00:13:44.840 --> 00:13:45.510
You never learn!

00:13:45.510 --> 00:13:47.440
Wait, wait. Just wait till I get up!

00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:49.000
Will you learn your lesson?

00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:50.360
Don't move. Why won't you learn?

00:13:50.360 --> 00:13:51.360
Xiaoman, get up!

00:13:51.670 --> 00:13:52.730
What are you doing?

00:13:53.630 --> 00:13:54.960
What are you doing here?

00:13:55.080 --> 00:13:55.830
Get up.

00:13:56.800 --> 00:13:57.530
Does it hurt?

00:13:57.530 --> 00:13:59.360
No one wants to steal your business.

00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:01.480
There are only so many jobs, right?

00:14:01.600 --> 00:14:03.670
We are just competing fairly.

00:14:04.270 --> 00:14:06.050
I'm letting this slide
for Mr. Ding's sake.

00:14:06.050 --> 00:14:06.930
Just you wait.

00:14:10.240 --> 00:14:11.120
Mr. Zhuang!

00:14:11.750 --> 00:14:12.810
What are you doing?

00:14:15.630 --> 00:14:16.390
Stop.

00:14:16.390 --> 00:14:17.880
Chief Engineer Yan is missing.

00:14:17.880 --> 00:14:18.390
What?

00:14:18.480 --> 00:14:20.390
Chief Engineer Yan is missing!

00:14:20.550 --> 00:14:21.680
When did he get lost?

00:14:22.670 --> 00:14:24.120
We went to dig for wild vegetables.

00:14:24.120 --> 00:14:25.200
Chief Engineer Yan saw us

00:14:25.200 --> 00:14:26.500
and insisted on coming along.

00:14:26.500 --> 00:14:27.560
But halfway there,

00:14:27.600 --> 00:14:28.590
the car ran out of gas.

00:14:28.590 --> 00:14:29.480
The driver went to get gas

00:14:29.480 --> 00:14:30.810
and told us to walk back.

00:14:30.910 --> 00:14:32.040
But when we got back,

00:14:32.200 --> 00:14:33.720
we couldn't find Chief Engineer Yan.

00:14:33.720 --> 00:14:35.250
None of us saw where he went.

00:14:37.220 --> 00:14:38.270
Xiaodan told me

00:14:38.720 --> 00:14:41.160
her father
has Alzheimer's and gets confused.

00:14:41.160 --> 00:14:43.010
That was when I found out he was sick.

00:14:43.010 --> 00:14:44.340
They told me to wait here

00:14:44.350 --> 00:14:46.630
and keep Chief Engineer Yan here
if he comes back.

00:14:46.630 --> 00:14:47.750
What a mess.

00:14:47.750 --> 00:14:49.200
Where are we going?

00:14:49.200 --> 00:14:50.130
To visit a grave.

00:14:50.510 --> 00:14:51.840
Those little bastards.

00:14:51.900 --> 00:14:53.830
We'll be exhausted if we walk back.

00:14:56.470 --> 00:14:57.870
Visiting a grave is good.

00:14:58.440 --> 00:15:00.770
I didn't go during the Qingming Festival.

00:15:01.670 --> 00:15:03.550
I should go see my old friends.

00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:05.080
I remember now.

00:15:05.080 --> 00:15:07.320
Chief Engineer Yan asked me
where we were going.

00:15:07.320 --> 00:15:10.120
I was angry,
so I said we were going to visit a grave.

00:15:10.630 --> 00:15:13.360
It's okay, sir.
Don't worry. I'll go look for him.

00:15:14.210 --> 00:15:16.540
-Do Xia Lei and the others know?
-Xiaodan.

00:15:16.630 --> 00:15:19.600
I just told them.
They went to look for him too.

00:15:19.600 --> 00:15:20.320
Okay, okay. It's fine.

00:15:20.320 --> 00:15:21.050
Don't worry.

00:15:21.750 --> 00:15:22.440
It's okay.

00:15:22.730 --> 00:15:23.720
Look how worried you are.

00:15:23.720 --> 00:15:24.870
It's okay, sir. Don't worry.

00:15:24.870 --> 00:15:26.150
-Xia Lei.
-He will find him.

00:15:26.150 --> 00:15:26.550
Don't worry.

00:15:26.550 --> 00:15:27.910
Chief Engineer Yan is missing, right?

00:15:27.910 --> 00:15:28.540
It's okay.

00:15:28.750 --> 00:15:31.510
He probably went to the cemetery
on the back hill.

00:15:32.910 --> 00:15:34.440
I'll head over there first.

00:15:34.960 --> 00:15:36.840
Okay. Don't worry. Okay.

00:15:38.390 --> 00:15:40.300
Go home. It's fine, I'll go look for him.

00:15:40.300 --> 00:15:41.790
The three of us will go look for him.
Don't worry.

00:15:41.790 --> 00:15:42.580
Go back now.

00:15:49.220 --> 00:15:50.950
I know you blame me.

00:15:52.910 --> 00:15:53.480
Bro.

00:15:53.720 --> 00:15:54.270
Bro.

00:15:54.390 --> 00:15:55.400
He blames me.

00:15:55.420 --> 00:15:57.750
He doesn't. Aren't you two getting along?

00:15:58.850 --> 00:16:01.130
Because I haven't visited him in a while.

00:16:01.450 --> 00:16:01.790
[Late Zhao Cun]

00:16:01.790 --> 00:16:03.720
I was too ashamed to come.

00:16:06.120 --> 00:16:07.510
Sometimes I wonder,

00:16:08.080 --> 00:16:09.110
if back then,

00:16:09.790 --> 00:16:13.320
he had survived and I had died,

00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:18.100
he would have definitely stayed
with this plant until the end.

00:16:18.100 --> 00:16:19.630
Let's not think about that.

00:16:19.730 --> 00:16:21.720
Bro, we're doing fine now.

00:16:21.720 --> 00:16:22.510
Why dwell on it?

00:16:22.510 --> 00:16:23.910
You don't know him.

00:16:25.910 --> 00:16:27.190
He's our brother.

00:16:27.210 --> 00:16:27.780
Yes.

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:30.280
We joined the plant in the same year.

00:16:30.310 --> 00:16:30.910
I know.

00:16:30.960 --> 00:16:33.200
That... Dalin?

00:16:33.200 --> 00:16:33.720
Zhuang Dalin.

00:16:33.720 --> 00:16:34.720
Zhuang Dalin's senior.

00:16:34.720 --> 00:16:35.080
Right.

00:16:35.080 --> 00:16:37.810
He was the best technician
in our plant back then.

00:16:41.360 --> 00:16:43.030
Don't just stare. Bow to him.

00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:44.630
Right.

00:16:44.790 --> 00:16:45.840
Do I have to teach you everything?

00:16:45.840 --> 00:16:46.910
We came to see you.

00:16:47.020 --> 00:16:48.220
We're here to see you.

00:16:49.630 --> 00:16:50.870
You didn't bring any booze?

00:16:50.870 --> 00:16:51.550
I did.

00:16:51.720 --> 00:16:52.240
You did?

00:16:52.240 --> 00:16:53.360
It's right here.

00:16:54.270 --> 00:16:55.750
Let me get this cap off.

00:16:56.360 --> 00:16:57.420
Don't mess around.

00:17:02.870 --> 00:17:03.840
It's sauce-aroma baijiu.

00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:05.099
That's the good stuff.

00:17:07.300 --> 00:17:08.240
Let him have some.

00:17:08.240 --> 00:17:09.160
Just a little.

00:17:09.160 --> 00:17:10.480
Zhao couldn't hold his liquor.

00:17:10.480 --> 00:17:11.109
Just a little then.

00:17:11.109 --> 00:17:12.000
A sip is enough.

00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:13.109
Should I leave the bottle here for him?

00:17:13.109 --> 00:17:13.960
Leave it here.

00:17:13.960 --> 00:17:15.480
Our bro poured you a drink.

00:17:18.349 --> 00:17:19.750
I never expected this.

00:17:20.160 --> 00:17:22.829
When you moved to Shanghai,

00:17:23.310 --> 00:17:25.400
I thought we'd never meet again.

00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:28.030
I didn't expect
that we'd be able to have a drink together

00:17:28.030 --> 00:17:29.160
and talk.

00:17:30.680 --> 00:17:32.110
It's fine. We're close by anyway.

00:17:32.110 --> 00:17:34.400
Right? We can come by when we're free.

00:17:34.400 --> 00:17:34.920
Right.

00:17:34.920 --> 00:17:35.830
Whenever the weather is nice,

00:17:35.830 --> 00:17:37.400
just give me a call, and we'll come over.

00:17:37.400 --> 00:17:37.830
Okay.

00:17:37.830 --> 00:17:38.400
Okay?

00:17:38.830 --> 00:17:40.960
So let's head back for today, alright?

00:17:41.310 --> 00:17:42.240
We're going back?

00:17:42.240 --> 00:17:43.200
Time to cook.

00:17:43.410 --> 00:17:44.200
Time to cook.

00:17:44.850 --> 00:17:45.440
Alright.

00:17:45.470 --> 00:17:46.110
Let's go.

00:17:46.110 --> 00:17:47.000
Let's go.

00:17:47.200 --> 00:17:47.550
Okay.

00:17:47.550 --> 00:17:48.750
Let's go home to cook.

00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:52.720
Zhao,

00:17:53.880 --> 00:17:55.310
I'm heading back.

00:17:55.740 --> 00:17:56.260
See you.

00:17:56.280 --> 00:17:56.810
Let's go.

00:17:56.880 --> 00:17:57.680
Let's go home.

00:17:58.590 --> 00:17:59.390
Let's go home.

00:17:59.860 --> 00:18:00.490
Xiaoman.

00:18:05.910 --> 00:18:07.040
Where have you been?

00:18:07.270 --> 00:18:09.260
I've been looking everywhere for you.

00:18:09.260 --> 00:18:10.480
Who was looking for whom?

00:18:10.480 --> 00:18:12.280
I was looking for you, of course.

00:18:12.390 --> 00:18:13.920
You're causing trouble again.

00:18:13.920 --> 00:18:15.790
Not only did you skip school,
but you came here to play.

00:18:15.790 --> 00:18:16.590
It's dangerous here.

00:18:16.590 --> 00:18:17.510
What if something happens to you?

00:18:17.510 --> 00:18:18.030
No, Uncle.

00:18:18.030 --> 00:18:19.030
We were doing an extracurricular activity.

00:18:19.030 --> 00:18:20.110
She just got lost.

00:18:20.110 --> 00:18:21.040
We found her now.

00:18:21.070 --> 00:18:21.830
Extracurricular activity?

00:18:21.830 --> 00:18:22.350
Yes.

00:18:22.480 --> 00:18:23.350
Extracurricular activity?

00:18:23.350 --> 00:18:24.160
Right.

00:18:25.980 --> 00:18:26.980
Who is this girl?

00:18:28.240 --> 00:18:28.960
For the extracurricular activity...

00:18:28.960 --> 00:18:29.920
I am their classmate.

00:18:29.920 --> 00:18:30.790
They came to find me.

00:18:30.790 --> 00:18:31.880
Right. She's in the class next door.

00:18:31.880 --> 00:18:33.280
How come I don't know her?

00:18:34.270 --> 00:18:35.680
You didn't lead them astray, did you?

00:18:35.680 --> 00:18:36.790
That wasn't me.

00:18:36.960 --> 00:18:38.680
Bro, the kids are just playing.

00:18:38.680 --> 00:18:39.440
It's okay.

00:18:39.440 --> 00:18:40.200
Let's go home to eat.

00:18:40.200 --> 00:18:40.590
Let's go home to eat.

00:18:40.590 --> 00:18:41.400
I'll take you home.

00:18:41.400 --> 00:18:41.990
Let's go home!

00:18:41.990 --> 00:18:42.660
Let's go home to eat!

00:18:42.660 --> 00:18:43.350
Let's go home.

00:18:43.350 --> 00:18:44.180
March forward!

00:18:44.180 --> 00:18:45.030
I'll carry your clothes.

00:18:45.030 --> 00:18:45.590
Okay.

00:18:47.860 --> 00:18:49.590
How did you know my dad was here?

00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:51.480
We chat all the time.

00:18:52.200 --> 00:18:54.070
When I heard Uncle Yan was lost,

00:18:54.070 --> 00:18:55.160
I came right away.

00:18:58.350 --> 00:18:59.160
Thank you.

00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:00.560
No problem. We found him.

00:19:00.560 --> 00:19:02.820
If you can't find him again, just tell me.

00:19:08.590 --> 00:19:10.650
Are these people all from your plant?

00:19:13.350 --> 00:19:14.480
It has been decades.

00:19:14.880 --> 00:19:16.810
Those who have passed are all here.

00:19:17.260 --> 00:19:19.630
I wonder where they all came from.

00:19:20.510 --> 00:19:21.790
I wonder if they have

00:19:21.790 --> 00:19:22.720
any family left

00:19:22.720 --> 00:19:23.720
to visit them now.

00:19:25.270 --> 00:19:26.160
Back then,

00:19:26.200 --> 00:19:28.520
some people

00:19:28.630 --> 00:19:30.690
brought their whole families along.

00:19:30.880 --> 00:19:31.840
Others

00:19:31.960 --> 00:19:33.720
might have just come alone.

00:19:34.550 --> 00:19:37.630
But in the end,
they all stayed at our plant.

00:19:39.510 --> 00:19:41.550
It's nice that everyone is together.

00:19:41.550 --> 00:19:43.150
At least they aren't lonely.

00:19:45.030 --> 00:19:45.720
Let's go.

00:19:46.390 --> 00:19:48.240
Hold your own clothes.
Don't just toss them.

00:19:48.240 --> 00:19:48.770
Let's go.

00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:50.590
Let's go.

00:19:54.950 --> 00:20:01.220
♪ I came to the street ♪

00:20:01.960 --> 00:20:02.960
Dad, to the right.

00:20:03.680 --> 00:20:04.240
I know.

00:20:05.160 --> 00:20:06.680
♪ Listen from the beginning ♪

00:20:07.680 --> 00:20:08.590
Who is this?

00:20:09.590 --> 00:20:11.590
♪ They are no bandits ♪

00:20:11.750 --> 00:20:13.440
Mr. Zhuang, why are you still here?

00:20:13.440 --> 00:20:14.350
What are you doing here?

00:20:14.350 --> 00:20:15.310
I was worried.

00:20:15.830 --> 00:20:16.980
Yan...

00:20:17.950 --> 00:20:18.950
He...

00:20:21.160 --> 00:20:22.590
I can find my way back.

00:20:22.700 --> 00:20:23.830
They're just meddling.

00:20:23.830 --> 00:20:25.270
They were worrying for nothing.

00:20:25.270 --> 00:20:26.440
Don't worry, I'm fine.

00:20:26.440 --> 00:20:27.480
See? I'm back.

00:20:27.480 --> 00:20:29.200
How could I not find my own home?

00:20:29.200 --> 00:20:31.350
♪ They are no bandits ♪

00:20:31.880 --> 00:20:33.310
It's good that he's back.

00:20:33.750 --> 00:20:35.810
I couldn't bear the responsibility.

00:20:35.810 --> 00:20:36.790
It's okay. Don't worry.

00:20:36.790 --> 00:20:37.880
He's...

00:20:38.540 --> 00:20:39.540
He's fine now.

00:20:40.030 --> 00:20:42.230
Mr. Zhuang, why don't you go back first?

00:20:42.400 --> 00:20:44.000
Take good care of your dad.

00:20:44.270 --> 00:20:45.330
I'll head back now.

00:20:45.910 --> 00:20:46.740
Go ahead.

00:20:47.830 --> 00:20:48.510
You should go back now.

00:20:48.510 --> 00:20:50.110
Your family must be worried.

00:20:54.750 --> 00:20:55.350
Take care.

00:21:00.350 --> 00:21:00.940
Let's go.

00:21:07.310 --> 00:21:08.370
Move forward a bit.

00:21:08.510 --> 00:21:09.770
Move forward. Come on.

00:21:09.930 --> 00:21:10.680
Go down.

00:21:10.750 --> 00:21:11.550
Come this way.

00:21:14.400 --> 00:21:15.130
Is that okay?

00:21:15.830 --> 00:21:16.640
Forward a little more.

00:21:16.640 --> 00:21:17.880
Okay.

00:21:22.730 --> 00:21:24.350
Are you Manyi Moving Company?

00:21:24.350 --> 00:21:25.910
I called you just now.

00:21:25.940 --> 00:21:27.040
You called us?

00:21:27.510 --> 00:21:28.590
It's 500 yuan, right?

00:21:28.590 --> 00:21:30.240
You won't raise the price, will you?

00:21:30.240 --> 00:21:32.210
No extra charge.
We stick to the agreed price.

00:21:32.210 --> 00:21:32.820
Alright.

00:21:33.030 --> 00:21:34.440
So, this is our stuff.

00:21:34.440 --> 00:21:35.000
These things.

00:21:35.000 --> 00:21:35.720
Let's get to it.

00:21:35.720 --> 00:21:36.380
Don't move!

00:21:37.680 --> 00:21:38.810
Zhang Xiaoman.

00:21:39.340 --> 00:21:41.030
Enemies really do cross paths.

00:21:41.030 --> 00:21:41.920
So annoying.

00:21:42.360 --> 00:21:43.710
This job is mine.

00:21:44.750 --> 00:21:45.790
You stay out of it.

00:21:46.790 --> 00:21:48.880
Jinlong, what is wrong with you?

00:21:49.340 --> 00:21:50.350
Do you have maggots on you?

00:21:50.350 --> 00:21:51.960
Why are you always acting weird with me?

00:21:51.960 --> 00:21:53.830
Don't give me that smart mouth.

00:21:54.110 --> 00:21:55.630
This job is mine.

00:21:55.720 --> 00:21:57.070
Don't try to steal it.

00:21:57.090 --> 00:21:58.480
What do you mean it's yours?

00:21:58.480 --> 00:21:59.550
They approached me.

00:21:59.550 --> 00:22:00.880
They called me.

00:22:01.200 --> 00:22:02.480
Can you be reasonable?

00:22:02.480 --> 00:22:03.830
They called me first.

00:22:04.680 --> 00:22:05.140
Well...

00:22:06.830 --> 00:22:09.480
Yes, I called them first.

00:22:09.920 --> 00:22:12.050
I even paid half the price as a deposit.

00:22:12.160 --> 00:22:15.480
But as soon as they moved things down,
they jacked up the price,

00:22:15.480 --> 00:22:17.270
asking for an upstairs fee

00:22:17.270 --> 00:22:18.640
and a labor fee.

00:22:18.640 --> 00:22:20.720
1,200 yuan out of nowhere.

00:22:20.720 --> 00:22:22.640
I said I could only add 500.

00:22:22.640 --> 00:22:23.750
But he refused.

00:22:24.050 --> 00:22:25.510
That's why I called you.

00:22:25.510 --> 00:22:27.720
Why do you guys always pull this crap?

00:22:27.880 --> 00:22:28.750
Price gouging?

00:22:29.310 --> 00:22:29.960
What?

00:22:30.030 --> 00:22:31.350
Trying to be the scum of the industry?

00:22:31.350 --> 00:22:32.720
Don't act like a saint here.

00:22:32.720 --> 00:22:35.110
1,200. Not a penny less.

00:22:35.480 --> 00:22:36.240
1,200?

00:22:36.240 --> 00:22:37.590
Must be 1,200.

00:22:37.790 --> 00:22:38.830
Or you won't do it, right?

00:22:38.830 --> 00:22:39.400
Yes.

00:22:39.400 --> 00:22:40.160
We'll do it.

00:22:40.400 --> 00:22:40.880
Come on.

00:22:40.880 --> 00:22:42.750
We'll do it. I'm taking this job, okay?

00:22:42.750 --> 00:22:43.320
Step aside.

00:22:43.320 --> 00:22:44.180
You're fired. Come on.

00:22:44.180 --> 00:22:45.040
Zhang Xiaoman.

00:22:45.790 --> 00:22:47.030
You really dare to steal my job?

00:22:47.030 --> 00:22:47.550
What?

00:22:47.550 --> 00:22:48.640
You want to fight?

00:22:48.750 --> 00:22:49.510
You want a fight?

00:22:49.510 --> 00:22:50.030
Yes.

00:22:50.440 --> 00:22:51.900
I'll fix you up good today.

00:22:52.110 --> 00:22:53.350
Call for backup. Hurry.

00:22:53.350 --> 00:22:54.110
-Don't leave.
-Do it.

00:22:54.110 --> 00:22:54.830
Alright. We're not leaving.

00:22:54.830 --> 00:22:55.160
Do it. Do it.

00:22:55.160 --> 00:22:55.750
Stay right here. Do you hear me?

00:22:55.750 --> 00:22:56.640
I'd like to see who you call.

00:22:56.640 --> 00:22:57.550
My gosh, look at you acting tough.

00:22:57.550 --> 00:22:58.920
Your name is Wang Jinlong, right?

00:22:58.920 --> 00:22:59.830
Yes, Wang Jinlong.

00:22:59.830 --> 00:23:00.920
Yes, Wang Jinlong.

00:23:01.350 --> 00:23:02.000
Pretty tough.

00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:02.750
Yeah, tough.

00:23:02.750 --> 00:23:03.480
Please come over.

00:23:03.480 --> 00:23:04.510
Alright. Who are you calling?

00:23:04.510 --> 00:23:05.170
The police.

00:23:07.590 --> 00:23:08.070
Hello?

00:23:08.090 --> 00:23:08.980
Uh, Officer.

00:23:09.040 --> 00:23:10.160
We called the wrong number.

00:23:10.160 --> 00:23:11.440
We were just messing around.

00:23:11.440 --> 00:23:11.830
Wrong number.

00:23:11.830 --> 00:23:12.830
Sorry about that.

00:23:14.770 --> 00:23:15.590
Alright. Let's go.

00:23:15.590 --> 00:23:16.370
-Jinlong.
-Just you wait!

00:23:16.370 --> 00:23:17.230
Don't touch me!

00:23:17.960 --> 00:23:18.550
Just you wait!

00:23:18.550 --> 00:23:19.310
Stay right here!

00:23:19.310 --> 00:23:21.110
All you can do is call the police.

00:23:23.160 --> 00:23:23.960
Zhuang, you're here?

00:23:23.960 --> 00:23:24.590
Come in, come in.

00:23:24.590 --> 00:23:25.510
I came to see Yan.

00:23:25.510 --> 00:23:26.110
Okay.

00:23:26.110 --> 00:23:26.880
Come in. Please.

00:23:26.880 --> 00:23:27.680
My son

00:23:27.680 --> 00:23:28.940
sent this from Hainan.

00:23:28.990 --> 00:23:30.510
It's some coconut juice. Sickly sweet.

00:23:30.510 --> 00:23:32.240
He said it's good for the brain.

00:23:33.030 --> 00:23:34.920
Zhuang Sen bought this for you.

00:23:34.920 --> 00:23:36.070
Why did you bring it to Yan?

00:23:36.070 --> 00:23:36.750
Sit down, sit down.

00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:38.210
It's good for Yan's brain.

00:23:39.080 --> 00:23:40.400
Okay, you guys talk.

00:23:40.680 --> 00:23:41.400
Okay.

00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:42.030
You guys talk.

00:23:42.030 --> 00:23:44.160
You haven't shown your face in a while.

00:23:46.160 --> 00:23:47.000
Let me tell you.

00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:47.480
Yan.

00:23:47.480 --> 00:23:49.160
With your high blood pressure...

00:23:49.160 --> 00:23:51.070
I came to apologize to you.

00:23:51.200 --> 00:23:52.310
Sometimes I speak

00:23:52.440 --> 00:23:53.830
without thinking.

00:23:53.850 --> 00:23:56.130
Don't take anything I said to heart.

00:23:58.880 --> 00:24:00.440
Wait. What did you say?

00:24:00.440 --> 00:24:01.480
You forgot?

00:24:03.340 --> 00:24:04.670
Forget I said anything.

00:24:04.880 --> 00:24:05.480
What?

00:24:07.110 --> 00:24:08.040
I didn't forget.

00:24:10.110 --> 00:24:11.510
You said I was a deserter.

00:24:12.680 --> 00:24:14.600
Don't listen to their nonsense.

00:24:14.620 --> 00:24:17.220
No, you said it yourself.

00:24:17.540 --> 00:24:18.740
I was wondering.

00:24:19.240 --> 00:24:21.110
I worked hard for our East Chemical Plant

00:24:21.110 --> 00:24:22.960
my whole life.

00:24:23.310 --> 00:24:26.000
How did I end up being a deserter?

00:24:28.510 --> 00:24:30.050
Then let me explain it for you.

00:24:30.050 --> 00:24:30.680
Go ahead.

00:24:31.880 --> 00:24:33.610
That year, after the accident,

00:24:33.880 --> 00:24:35.030
I didn't blame you.

00:24:35.440 --> 00:24:37.000
My senior didn't blame you either.

00:24:37.000 --> 00:24:38.730
You got promoted all the way up.

00:24:38.960 --> 00:24:40.110
You deserved that.

00:24:40.350 --> 00:24:41.270
But,

00:24:41.790 --> 00:24:44.720
when the big ship
of East Chemical Plant was sinking,

00:24:44.830 --> 00:24:46.560
you were the first to jump ship.

00:24:46.890 --> 00:24:48.790
You were the top technical expert.

00:24:48.790 --> 00:24:51.200
When you left, Director Meng left too.

00:24:52.240 --> 00:24:53.790
We old workers

00:24:53.920 --> 00:24:55.520
all had issues with you guys.

00:24:59.110 --> 00:25:01.720
You're talking about two different things.

00:25:03.590 --> 00:25:05.250
Let me explain them one by one.

00:25:06.880 --> 00:25:08.740
Let's talk about the first thing.

00:25:08.980 --> 00:25:10.110
After the accident,

00:25:11.160 --> 00:25:12.560
your senior passed away.

00:25:14.070 --> 00:25:16.310
Back then, I felt worse than anyone.

00:25:18.440 --> 00:25:19.770
But he was already dead.

00:25:20.790 --> 00:25:21.650
What could I do?

00:25:24.680 --> 00:25:28.270
You saw how I worked in the plant.

00:25:28.590 --> 00:25:30.440
Didn't I work myself to the bone?

00:25:30.580 --> 00:25:32.580
I did the work of several people.

00:25:33.680 --> 00:25:34.960
It's true that later on,

00:25:34.960 --> 00:25:37.220
they gave me the title of Chief Engineer.

00:25:37.350 --> 00:25:38.550
But whether I had that title or not,

00:25:38.550 --> 00:25:39.920
it didn't matter to me.

00:25:40.240 --> 00:25:41.700
What was I thinking about?

00:25:41.880 --> 00:25:43.410
Building up the plant well.

00:25:43.680 --> 00:25:46.350
That was the only way
to let our dead brothers rest in peace.

00:25:46.350 --> 00:25:46.960
Right?

00:25:47.720 --> 00:25:48.290
Okay.

00:25:49.750 --> 00:25:51.960
Let me tell you about the second thing.

00:25:51.960 --> 00:25:53.360
You said I was a deserter.

00:25:53.830 --> 00:25:56.220
I admit it. I ran away.

00:25:56.720 --> 00:25:59.750
The plant had stopped production
back then.

00:26:00.030 --> 00:26:00.880
I left.

00:26:01.400 --> 00:26:03.260
My whole family moved to Shanghai

00:26:03.680 --> 00:26:05.810
to be with my daughter for her studies.

00:26:09.480 --> 00:26:10.720
But you don't know,

00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:12.880
my heart...

00:26:13.590 --> 00:26:16.310
has never left the East Chemical Plant
for a single day.

00:26:16.310 --> 00:26:17.680
What I wanted was that

00:26:17.790 --> 00:26:19.310
once my daughter graduates,

00:26:19.310 --> 00:26:20.680
I'd come back—

00:26:20.680 --> 00:26:22.000
return to where I belong.

00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:23.830
When these old bones of mine die,

00:26:25.090 --> 00:26:27.150
I must die at the East Chemical Plant.

00:26:31.110 --> 00:26:32.680
I thought that now you're sick,

00:26:32.680 --> 00:26:33.700
you'd have forgotten all that.

00:26:33.700 --> 00:26:34.830
I won't forget that.

00:26:35.720 --> 00:26:37.030
I'll never forget.

00:26:37.720 --> 00:26:38.510
Yan,

00:26:39.200 --> 00:26:40.070
I was wrong.

00:26:40.550 --> 00:26:42.750
I shouldn't have called you a deserter.

00:26:43.560 --> 00:26:44.360
I was wrong.

00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:47.310
There's

00:26:47.890 --> 00:26:49.330
no right or wrong in this.

00:26:50.720 --> 00:26:51.960
You have grievances,

00:26:52.750 --> 00:26:55.480
and the brothers have grievances.
I understand.

00:26:56.590 --> 00:26:58.350
Today, let's just clear

00:26:58.680 --> 00:27:00.010
this knot in our hearts.

00:27:00.310 --> 00:27:01.160
It's decided then.

00:27:01.160 --> 00:27:02.030
I'm back.

00:27:02.960 --> 00:27:03.510
Mom, Dad.

00:27:03.510 --> 00:27:05.440
-Hello, Mrs. Yan.
-Xia Lei is here.

00:27:06.590 --> 00:27:07.830
You're here, brat.

00:27:08.120 --> 00:27:08.640
Sir.

00:27:09.110 --> 00:27:10.170
Listen to me, brat.

00:27:10.880 --> 00:27:12.540
You're having dinner at our house tonight.

00:27:12.540 --> 00:27:13.300
Okay?

00:27:13.660 --> 00:27:14.310
Xiaodan.

00:27:15.160 --> 00:27:16.820
Go buy a bottle of good liquor.

00:27:18.960 --> 00:27:19.760
Get up.

00:27:20.110 --> 00:27:22.440
The food's cooking
and you're just sleeping here.

00:27:22.440 --> 00:27:22.880
Time to eat.

00:27:22.880 --> 00:27:23.880
I was taking a nap.

00:27:27.590 --> 00:27:28.920
I have... I have an idea.

00:27:29.440 --> 00:27:30.750
I want to change

00:27:30.750 --> 00:27:33.830
how our moving company runs.

00:27:35.550 --> 00:27:36.880
I want to do...

00:27:38.350 --> 00:27:39.350
high-end moving.

00:27:39.640 --> 00:27:40.640
High-end moving?

00:27:41.400 --> 00:27:42.530
What does that mean?

00:27:43.070 --> 00:27:44.960
I saw it in Japan before.

00:27:44.960 --> 00:27:46.550
This kind of moving company

00:27:46.550 --> 00:27:48.400
doesn't just move your furniture

00:27:48.400 --> 00:27:49.310
and leave it at the new place.

00:27:49.310 --> 00:27:51.960
They start at your old home,

00:27:52.400 --> 00:27:54.720
noting all your habits,

00:27:54.720 --> 00:27:56.270
marking exactly

00:27:56.270 --> 00:27:57.830
where every piece of furniture goes,

00:27:57.830 --> 00:27:59.550
and packing up all your clothes, shoes,

00:27:59.550 --> 00:28:01.270
essentials, and miscellaneous stuff.

00:28:01.270 --> 00:28:02.640
Then at the new place,

00:28:02.830 --> 00:28:04.490
they put everything back
in its original spot—

00:28:04.490 --> 00:28:05.800
bedroom stuff in the bedroom,

00:28:05.800 --> 00:28:07.600
bathroom stuff in the bathroom.

00:28:07.750 --> 00:28:08.680
You don't have to worry about a thing.

00:28:08.680 --> 00:28:09.880
And once it's all done,

00:28:09.880 --> 00:28:11.200
they even do a thorough cleaning.

00:28:11.200 --> 00:28:11.960
That's great.

00:28:11.960 --> 00:28:13.090
A one-stop service.

00:28:15.920 --> 00:28:17.580
Zhang Xiaoman, get down here!

00:28:19.510 --> 00:28:21.170
Strip them. Strip the leaves.

00:28:21.750 --> 00:28:22.790
What are you doing?

00:28:22.790 --> 00:28:23.850
What are you doing?

00:28:25.270 --> 00:28:26.270
We had a deal.

00:28:26.750 --> 00:28:28.270
We stay out of each other's way.

00:28:28.270 --> 00:28:29.550
But you crossed the line immediately.

00:28:29.550 --> 00:28:30.590
What do you mean?

00:28:30.720 --> 00:28:31.880
What job did I steal from you?

00:28:31.880 --> 00:28:33.240
I didn't even charge that old lady.

00:28:33.240 --> 00:28:34.700
Stop playing dumb with me.

00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:36.030
I'm telling you,

00:28:36.110 --> 00:28:37.910
you won't walk out of here today.

00:28:38.590 --> 00:28:40.080
You're not gonna keep these plants!

00:28:40.080 --> 00:28:41.590
You're not! Bite me!

00:28:41.590 --> 00:28:43.250
Let go! What's wrong with you?

00:28:46.480 --> 00:28:47.680
You're tall and blocking the camera.

00:28:47.680 --> 00:28:48.540
Don't you know?

00:28:48.920 --> 00:28:51.120
Why are there so many people for moving?

00:28:55.880 --> 00:28:57.450
Xiaoman?

00:28:57.480 --> 00:28:58.240
Mr. Qu?

00:28:59.030 --> 00:28:59.750
Chunchun?

00:29:00.400 --> 00:29:01.000
Wait.

00:29:01.530 --> 00:29:02.820
It's your shop?

00:29:03.090 --> 00:29:03.660
Yes.

00:29:04.240 --> 00:29:04.750
Well...

00:29:06.780 --> 00:29:08.380
What are you guys doing here?

00:29:08.510 --> 00:29:09.070
Well...

00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:11.510
Well... we were just passing by.

00:29:11.510 --> 00:29:12.270
Passing by?

00:29:13.580 --> 00:29:15.560
So all these people were passing by?

00:29:15.560 --> 00:29:17.600
Well... I don't know them.

00:29:17.790 --> 00:29:20.750
I... I came to buy flowers.

00:29:21.030 --> 00:29:21.750
Who is he?

00:29:22.660 --> 00:29:24.680
He... he's from our plant.

00:29:24.680 --> 00:29:26.550
He often comes to chat with me.

00:29:26.830 --> 00:29:29.200
Right, right. We grew up together.

00:29:29.200 --> 00:29:30.790
We came to find Xiaoman

00:29:30.790 --> 00:29:32.050
to ch-chat for a while.

00:29:32.360 --> 00:29:33.270
Chat?

00:29:34.590 --> 00:29:35.650
Are you done chatting?

00:29:35.650 --> 00:29:36.590
Yes, yes.

00:29:36.590 --> 00:29:37.830
We're done. Let's go.

00:29:38.000 --> 00:29:38.920
Wanna chat a bit more?

00:29:38.920 --> 00:29:39.480
No.

00:29:39.640 --> 00:29:40.510
Bye, Xiaoman.

00:29:44.480 --> 00:29:45.750
Jinlong, Jinlong.

00:29:45.750 --> 00:29:46.920
What's this Zhang Xiaoman's background?

00:29:46.920 --> 00:29:48.050
Why is it... that...

00:29:48.270 --> 00:29:48.960
Keep it down.

00:29:48.960 --> 00:29:51.290
You scared me to death
coming in like that.

00:29:51.590 --> 00:29:52.390
Mr. Qu, you...

00:29:53.510 --> 00:29:55.070
You're not sick?

00:29:55.960 --> 00:29:57.090
Why should I be sick?

00:29:57.240 --> 00:29:57.960
Back at the hospital,

00:29:57.960 --> 00:30:00.070
I thought you were delusional.

00:30:00.200 --> 00:30:01.720
Turns out you were telling the truth.

00:30:01.720 --> 00:30:03.680
Delusional? Come on.

00:30:04.000 --> 00:30:05.750
I have bipolar disorder.

00:30:06.590 --> 00:30:08.160
I have business with you.

00:30:08.310 --> 00:30:10.960
I've already blown that hill flat.

00:30:10.960 --> 00:30:12.750
The digging there is almost done.

00:30:12.750 --> 00:30:13.680
You actually blew it up?

00:30:13.680 --> 00:30:16.110
Weren't you talking about building a...
hot spring pool?

00:30:16.110 --> 00:30:17.550
He was just talking nonsense.

00:30:17.550 --> 00:30:18.720
You're ridiculous!

00:30:18.720 --> 00:30:20.640
I was serious! You...

00:30:21.590 --> 00:30:23.200
Xiaoman, this business of yours—
I'm telling you—

00:30:23.200 --> 00:30:24.930
you made a good choice. Not bad.

00:30:25.480 --> 00:30:27.110
What a coincidence that you came here.

00:30:27.110 --> 00:30:28.000
Tell me about it.

00:30:28.000 --> 00:30:28.640
I saw online

00:30:28.640 --> 00:30:31.310
there's a Manyi Moving

00:30:31.310 --> 00:30:32.880
with good reviews.

00:30:32.880 --> 00:30:34.000
So, here I am.

00:30:34.000 --> 00:30:35.000
I need to move too.

00:30:35.110 --> 00:30:35.920
No problem.

00:30:36.200 --> 00:30:37.640
Today, Zhang Xiaoman was talking about

00:30:37.640 --> 00:30:39.400
some kind of
high-end and one-stop service—

00:30:39.400 --> 00:30:40.920
packing and cleaning included.

00:30:40.920 --> 00:30:42.030
You can try it.

00:30:42.110 --> 00:30:43.880
High-end moving? That's great.

00:30:43.880 --> 00:30:44.640
Come on.

00:30:49.220 --> 00:30:49.670
Here.

00:30:49.830 --> 00:30:51.160
What are you doing, Mr. Qu?

00:30:51.160 --> 00:30:52.090
It's for moving.

00:30:52.590 --> 00:30:53.440
Are you moving abroad?

00:30:53.440 --> 00:30:54.070
With all this money?

00:30:54.070 --> 00:30:55.510
Moving abroad?

00:30:55.510 --> 00:30:56.880
This is just a small token.

00:30:56.880 --> 00:30:58.290
You don't need this much, Mr. Qu.

00:30:58.290 --> 00:30:59.700
Why are you giving me all this money?

00:30:59.700 --> 00:31:00.740
It's not necessary.

00:31:00.740 --> 00:31:03.470
That's because you don't know
how big my house is.

00:31:03.990 --> 00:31:06.510
-Okay.
-I'll give you more if it's not enough.

00:31:06.510 --> 00:31:07.400
Alright.

00:31:07.400 --> 00:31:08.880
If there's nothing else,
I'll get going then.

00:31:08.880 --> 00:31:10.240
Don't go, Mr. Qu. Stay a while.

00:31:10.240 --> 00:31:11.480
I can't. I'm busy.

00:31:11.980 --> 00:31:15.030
Your dad was one of the first college graduates
trained in China after 1949.

00:31:15.030 --> 00:31:15.960
In the workshop,

00:31:16.790 --> 00:31:18.120
at East Chemical Plant,

00:31:18.200 --> 00:31:19.730
he was the cream of the crop.

00:31:20.550 --> 00:31:23.030
My senior was a talent.

00:31:23.960 --> 00:31:25.270
Whenever the plant selected
outstanding workers

00:31:25.270 --> 00:31:26.400
or model employees,

00:31:26.590 --> 00:31:28.850
the two of them were always neck and neck.

00:31:29.030 --> 00:31:30.290
Neither would give in.

00:31:30.830 --> 00:31:32.110
What did people in the workshop call them?

00:31:32.110 --> 00:31:35.480
Like in books... What's that saying?

00:31:35.480 --> 00:31:36.640
The...

00:31:36.640 --> 00:31:37.770
The Peerless Twins?

00:31:38.720 --> 00:31:39.830
Arch-rivals.

00:31:41.260 --> 00:31:42.520
Sit. Let's have a seat.

00:31:42.720 --> 00:31:43.640
You too.

00:31:43.750 --> 00:31:44.270
Okay.

00:31:47.640 --> 00:31:49.790
Mr. Zhuang, what about...

00:31:51.270 --> 00:31:53.400
that accident you mentioned?

00:31:57.270 --> 00:31:59.110
That was the biggest production accident

00:31:59.110 --> 00:32:00.920
since the plant was built.

00:32:01.160 --> 00:32:02.560
The day of the explosion,

00:32:03.000 --> 00:32:05.160
my senior and your dad were both there.

00:32:05.310 --> 00:32:07.510
The reactor's giant lid flew off

00:32:07.960 --> 00:32:09.510
and shielded them.

00:32:09.720 --> 00:32:11.680
Half a floor's worth of rubble

00:32:11.700 --> 00:32:12.980
buried them.

00:32:13.030 --> 00:32:15.000
We dug for a long, long time

00:32:15.780 --> 00:32:17.150
before we got them out.

00:32:18.160 --> 00:32:20.240
Your dad didn't have a scratch on him.

00:32:21.750 --> 00:32:22.830
But my senior

00:32:23.750 --> 00:32:24.830
wasn't shielded.

00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:27.010
He was crushed to death.

00:32:27.680 --> 00:32:28.940
I'm sorry, Mr. Zhuang.

00:32:28.970 --> 00:32:32.320
I didn't know that's what happened.

00:32:32.350 --> 00:32:34.200
We've talked it all out.

00:32:34.480 --> 00:32:36.030
I didn't blame your father,

00:32:36.160 --> 00:32:38.160
and my senior wouldn't have either.

00:32:38.400 --> 00:32:39.550
Your father's illness

00:32:39.550 --> 00:32:40.440
is in his head.

00:32:41.360 --> 00:32:43.190
He has to let it go himself.

00:32:44.510 --> 00:32:46.550
You should spend more time with him.

00:32:47.790 --> 00:32:48.590
You guys talk.

00:32:49.000 --> 00:32:50.260
I can get back on my own.

00:32:50.920 --> 00:32:51.750
-Let us see you off.
-We'll see you off.

00:32:51.750 --> 00:32:53.480
No need. I can get back on my own.

00:32:54.440 --> 00:32:54.900
Well...

00:32:58.270 --> 00:32:59.640
My generation...

00:33:00.830 --> 00:33:02.030
has deep feelings

00:33:03.720 --> 00:33:05.200
for East Chemical Plant.

00:33:15.230 --> 00:33:18.680
The friendship of the older generation
is really enviable.

00:33:19.400 --> 00:33:21.730
East Chemical Plant really is different.

00:33:22.240 --> 00:33:23.640
It's full of human touch.

00:33:23.880 --> 00:33:24.880
And it has warmth.

00:33:25.480 --> 00:33:26.480
Being in here,

00:33:27.270 --> 00:33:30.070
everything is so wonderful
that it's like a dream.

00:33:30.920 --> 00:33:33.840
When I started college, I told Xiaoman

00:33:35.920 --> 00:33:38.850
that our plant was different
from the outside world.

00:33:39.440 --> 00:33:41.920
At that time,
I couldn't explain it clearly.

00:33:41.920 --> 00:33:43.640
I couldn't describe that feeling,

00:33:43.640 --> 00:33:45.500
what that difference really was.

00:33:45.720 --> 00:33:48.750
It's just that...
Xiaoman could take a pair of chopsticks

00:33:48.750 --> 00:33:51.080
and get a full meal
at any neighbor's door.

00:33:51.270 --> 00:33:53.070
And look at my dad and Mr. Zhuang.

00:33:53.350 --> 00:33:54.790
For the sake of their senior,

00:33:54.790 --> 00:33:56.750
they'd protect the plant with their lives.

00:33:56.750 --> 00:33:59.750
This is the dream they built over decades.

00:34:00.160 --> 00:34:01.000
Look at me.

00:34:01.790 --> 00:34:04.190
I ended up studying architectural design.

00:34:04.270 --> 00:34:06.070
I want to keep my dream alive too.

00:34:06.880 --> 00:34:08.190
I want to pour my dream

00:34:10.630 --> 00:34:12.150
into my work.

00:34:14.070 --> 00:34:17.280
Through architecture,

00:34:18.630 --> 00:34:20.159
I want to solidify my dream,

00:34:20.710 --> 00:34:21.920
to protect it.

00:34:23.840 --> 00:34:25.360
I never thought about

00:34:26.190 --> 00:34:27.510
protecting a dream.

00:34:30.370 --> 00:34:32.960
I heard our plant is going to relocate.

00:34:32.989 --> 00:34:34.070
Is that true?

00:34:34.469 --> 00:34:35.199
I don't know.

00:34:35.550 --> 00:34:37.409
I heard it while I was out working.

00:34:37.469 --> 00:34:39.150
The Tiecheng government
made the final call.

00:34:39.150 --> 00:34:41.400
They say some people

00:34:41.400 --> 00:34:43.000
can buy out their seniority.

00:34:43.230 --> 00:34:44.110
And some people

00:34:45.030 --> 00:34:46.670
can go to Yingkou.

00:34:47.480 --> 00:34:50.770
But we're still on the plant payroll.

00:34:50.800 --> 00:34:51.710
What do you think?

00:34:51.710 --> 00:34:52.440
What do I think?

00:34:52.440 --> 00:34:53.639
Just stay put for now.

00:34:54.300 --> 00:34:57.230
I heard a customer at the dance hall
say the other day,

00:34:58.280 --> 00:35:01.360
that a group of people
don't want to leave,

00:35:01.360 --> 00:35:02.840
so they're looking for someone
to buy the plant.

00:35:02.840 --> 00:35:04.100
If someone takes over,

00:35:04.360 --> 00:35:05.920
the plant can keep running.

00:35:06.670 --> 00:35:09.550
Otherwise,
everyone gets a severance package

00:35:09.550 --> 00:35:11.210
and goes their separate ways.

00:35:11.440 --> 00:35:13.410
Xiaoman, haven't you heard?

00:35:13.480 --> 00:35:14.960
They say several people are in talks,

00:35:14.960 --> 00:35:16.590
including that classmate of yours,

00:35:16.590 --> 00:35:17.280
Xia Lei.

00:35:17.630 --> 00:35:18.800
He's in talks too.

00:35:19.030 --> 00:35:20.790
You don't have any insider info?

00:35:20.790 --> 00:35:22.000
-Xia Lei?
-I don't know.

00:35:22.000 --> 00:35:23.000
He didn't tell me.

00:35:23.510 --> 00:35:25.400
Anyway, my thought is,

00:35:25.880 --> 00:35:28.280
let's not worry about the plant.

00:35:29.550 --> 00:35:31.630
We can't do anything about it anyway.

00:35:31.810 --> 00:35:33.190
We haven't starved all these years,
have we?

00:35:33.190 --> 00:35:34.790
We've supported ourselves.

00:35:35.400 --> 00:35:37.280
As long as we keep doing our business well

00:35:37.280 --> 00:35:40.510
and earn enough to support our families,
that's enough.

00:35:41.360 --> 00:35:41.920
But...

00:35:43.110 --> 00:35:43.670
Home—

00:35:45.110 --> 00:35:46.110
we can't be without it.

00:35:46.110 --> 00:35:47.440
We must come back often.

00:35:47.840 --> 00:35:48.670
I like that.

00:35:49.360 --> 00:35:51.440
We can't be without a home.

00:35:51.480 --> 00:35:52.230
Well said!

00:35:52.280 --> 00:35:53.140
-Here!
-Bravo!

00:35:53.710 --> 00:35:54.190
It...

00:35:55.280 --> 00:35:57.280
It feels like I'm getting applause.

00:36:04.800 --> 00:36:05.440
Director.

00:36:06.190 --> 00:36:08.630
Regarding the acquisition of your plant,

00:36:08.630 --> 00:36:11.710
can we proceed with it?

00:36:12.630 --> 00:36:13.320
Mr. Yu,

00:36:13.490 --> 00:36:14.490
here's the thing.

00:36:15.030 --> 00:36:17.160
The City Investment Promotion Office

00:36:17.190 --> 00:36:18.510
has introduced a few enterprises

00:36:18.510 --> 00:36:20.480
to revitalize these assets.

00:36:20.960 --> 00:36:25.070
The higher-ups are currently studying
the proposals

00:36:25.070 --> 00:36:26.600
to see if they are feasible.

00:36:27.070 --> 00:36:30.320
But as for the feasibility of your plan...

00:36:31.840 --> 00:36:32.900
it isn't very high.

00:36:36.360 --> 00:36:38.440
My plan isn't feasible?

00:36:39.190 --> 00:36:41.710
How is my plan not feasible?

00:36:42.280 --> 00:36:43.610
Is the money not enough?

00:36:43.670 --> 00:36:46.840
Or do you have other difficulties?

00:36:47.950 --> 00:36:49.910
We are considered a major enterprise.

00:36:49.910 --> 00:36:50.540
Yes, it is.

00:36:50.760 --> 00:36:52.190
Just be honest with me.

00:36:52.190 --> 00:36:53.110
If there are any difficulties,

00:36:53.110 --> 00:36:55.360
like financial issues,

00:36:55.360 --> 00:36:57.190
we can put our cards on the table.

00:36:57.190 --> 00:36:57.800
No, no, no, Mr. Yu.

00:36:57.800 --> 00:36:59.000
Speak your mind.

00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:01.400
Otherwise, I'd think you're making up lies

00:37:02.070 --> 00:37:03.920
to jack up the price on me.

00:37:06.000 --> 00:37:06.880
Just kidding.

00:37:08.510 --> 00:37:09.190
Director.

00:37:12.360 --> 00:37:13.840
Oh, you have a guest?

00:37:14.360 --> 00:37:15.620
Do you need something?

00:37:16.630 --> 00:37:17.480
Yes, I do.

00:37:17.480 --> 00:37:19.150
Then wait for me outside for a moment.

00:37:19.150 --> 00:37:19.670
Okay.

00:37:21.230 --> 00:37:22.670
I'll be honest with you.

00:37:22.670 --> 00:37:26.280
There's an executive
of a foreign enterprise

00:37:26.400 --> 00:37:29.320
who grew up in this plant community.

00:37:29.360 --> 00:37:30.480
How could someone from here

00:37:30.480 --> 00:37:32.590
not care about his own plant?

00:37:32.630 --> 00:37:34.800
So, our plant

00:37:34.830 --> 00:37:37.490
has the potential
to be revitalized at any time.

00:37:39.480 --> 00:37:41.510
Yu, actually,

00:37:41.570 --> 00:37:43.610
our priority is employment.

00:37:44.230 --> 00:37:46.070
It concerns people's livelihoods

00:37:46.070 --> 00:37:48.110
and the development of the region.

00:37:48.440 --> 00:37:49.360
If right now,

00:37:49.360 --> 00:37:51.960
I just snap my fingers
and sell the plant to you,

00:37:52.480 --> 00:37:54.030
I can't bear that responsibility.

00:37:54.030 --> 00:37:55.560
It would be a loss of assets.

00:37:56.670 --> 00:37:57.920
Loss of assets?

00:38:02.320 --> 00:38:03.400
To be honest,

00:38:03.400 --> 00:38:04.590
I've toured your plant

00:38:04.590 --> 00:38:05.280
and seen it for myself.

00:38:05.280 --> 00:38:08.190
Can that pile of junk you have

00:38:08.590 --> 00:38:10.000
really be called assets?

00:38:12.510 --> 00:38:15.030
I'm here to help you solve your problems.

00:38:15.030 --> 00:38:15.760
Right?

00:38:16.040 --> 00:38:17.230
If you don't sell it to me,

00:38:17.230 --> 00:38:18.750
who else

00:38:19.260 --> 00:38:20.670
would come to such a place

00:38:20.670 --> 00:38:21.840
to buy your plant?

00:38:23.150 --> 00:38:24.190
No one, right?

00:38:24.880 --> 00:38:26.400
Mr. Yu, there is one.

00:38:26.790 --> 00:38:27.880
-There is?
-Now... Yes.

00:38:27.880 --> 00:38:30.840
It's the person in charge of Fenlier,

00:38:31.320 --> 00:38:32.070
Xia Lei.

00:38:32.470 --> 00:38:34.530
He's inspecting our plant right now.

00:38:35.090 --> 00:38:35.940
Xia Lei?

00:38:36.170 --> 00:38:36.730
Yes.

00:38:37.630 --> 00:38:38.960
Is that...

00:38:38.960 --> 00:38:41.280
the top student who came from our plant?

00:38:41.280 --> 00:38:41.920
That Xia Lei?

00:38:41.920 --> 00:38:42.580
That's him.

00:38:42.610 --> 00:38:43.740
You know him?

00:38:43.800 --> 00:38:45.070
I don't know him well.

00:38:45.070 --> 00:38:46.670
He...

00:38:47.280 --> 00:38:50.110
is a childhood friend of Xiaoman.

00:38:52.150 --> 00:38:53.070
Xiaoman?

00:38:55.360 --> 00:38:56.320
You see, Mr. Yu.

00:38:57.720 --> 00:38:59.120
I didn't lie to you, did I?

00:38:59.800 --> 00:39:00.510
Director.

00:39:02.440 --> 00:39:04.070
I really have spent

00:39:04.750 --> 00:39:06.660
half a year on this.

00:39:06.710 --> 00:39:08.840
And then today you suddenly tell me

00:39:08.840 --> 00:39:10.840
some nobody

00:39:10.840 --> 00:39:12.900
says they're going to revitalize it.

00:39:13.130 --> 00:39:14.530
How?

00:39:14.710 --> 00:39:16.960
If it could be revitalized,
it would have been.

00:39:16.960 --> 00:39:18.440
You wouldn't be waiting until now.

00:39:18.440 --> 00:39:19.050
Yes.

00:39:19.080 --> 00:39:19.730
Alright?

00:39:20.510 --> 00:39:21.840
I'll be waiting for your news then.

00:39:21.840 --> 00:39:22.710
Okay.

00:39:33.630 --> 00:39:35.400
What is that smell?

00:39:38.420 --> 00:39:39.250
Yu, look.

00:39:39.920 --> 00:39:41.550
They are all workers waiting for the news.

00:39:41.550 --> 00:39:42.840
I was born and raised here.

00:39:42.840 --> 00:39:44.070
Don't I know it?

00:39:44.070 --> 00:39:45.070
It can't be revitalized.

00:39:45.070 --> 00:39:45.920
So I think,

00:39:46.030 --> 00:39:47.430
we should just let it die.

00:39:47.440 --> 00:39:49.760
Director, you know my family's situation.

00:39:49.760 --> 00:39:51.030
I was laid off temporarily back then.

00:39:51.030 --> 00:39:52.400
I was grateful Factory No. 3 took me in.

00:39:52.400 --> 00:39:53.190
I thought from then on,

00:39:53.190 --> 00:39:54.440
I would work hard for the plant

00:39:54.440 --> 00:39:56.030
and do whatever you ask me to do.

00:39:56.030 --> 00:39:58.670
I didn't expect
Factory No. 3 to be shut down as well.

00:39:58.670 --> 00:40:00.070
No, Shi.

00:40:00.190 --> 00:40:02.400
The policy about our plant
hasn't come out yet.

00:40:02.400 --> 00:40:03.150
Don't worry.

00:40:03.150 --> 00:40:05.760
I can't give you an answer right now.

00:40:07.480 --> 00:40:09.550
Director, how can I not be worried?

00:40:09.550 --> 00:40:10.840
My wife is from the neighboring village.

00:40:10.840 --> 00:40:11.510
My parents are here too.

00:40:11.510 --> 00:40:12.710
I really can't leave.

00:40:13.190 --> 00:40:15.150
Director,
the day I joined the plant, I thought,

00:40:15.150 --> 00:40:16.070
I, Shi Dongming,

00:40:16.070 --> 00:40:17.760
would work for the plant all my life.

00:40:17.760 --> 00:40:19.220
I'd do whatever I was told.

00:40:19.630 --> 00:40:21.510
But now, before it's even the end,

00:40:21.510 --> 00:40:22.550
you've abandoned me

00:40:22.550 --> 00:40:24.030
and given up. What's that about?

00:40:24.030 --> 00:40:26.710
Who said we've given up, Shi?

00:40:26.710 --> 00:40:28.800
What do you think I'm doing right now?

00:40:28.920 --> 00:40:30.230
What I'm doing now

00:40:30.230 --> 00:40:32.150
is to ensure every worker in our plant

00:40:32.150 --> 00:40:33.920
gets a good outcome.

00:40:34.280 --> 00:40:35.150
I promise you.

00:40:35.770 --> 00:40:37.930
As long as one worker is unsettled,

00:40:38.230 --> 00:40:39.030
I won't leave.

00:40:39.800 --> 00:40:41.730
Director, I trust your character.

00:40:42.480 --> 00:40:43.480
I just want...

00:40:44.000 --> 00:40:45.710
I just want a definite time.

00:40:45.710 --> 00:40:47.000
I just want exact information.

00:40:47.000 --> 00:40:47.960
It's just... I...

00:40:47.960 --> 00:40:49.960
It'll be soon. It'll be soon.

00:40:50.110 --> 00:40:51.030
Alright? I'm begging you,

00:40:51.030 --> 00:40:52.630
please leave.

00:40:57.320 --> 00:40:59.590
Repeat what you just told me

00:41:00.480 --> 00:41:03.230
to the others in the plant.

00:41:05.630 --> 00:41:06.320
Alright.

00:41:06.400 --> 00:41:10.800
Also, let that arrogant,

00:41:10.820 --> 00:41:11.940
stupid guy—

00:41:12.230 --> 00:41:13.960
what did the Plant Director
say his name was?

00:41:13.960 --> 00:41:14.510
Xia Lei.

00:41:14.510 --> 00:41:16.880
Right. Let Xia Lei know too,

00:41:17.590 --> 00:41:18.880
so he backs off.

00:41:20.360 --> 00:41:20.800
Okay.

00:41:22.360 --> 00:41:23.150
Shi.

00:41:24.590 --> 00:41:28.320
It's me, Zhigang. Do you remember me?

00:41:29.280 --> 00:41:30.440
I know who you are.

00:41:31.400 --> 00:41:32.320
Everyone at the East Chemical Plant

00:41:32.320 --> 00:41:33.670
knows someone like you.

00:41:33.920 --> 00:41:35.230
Come on. What are you doing?

00:41:35.230 --> 00:41:36.320
I wanted to talk to you about

00:41:36.320 --> 00:41:37.400
the acquisition of Factory No. 3.

00:41:37.400 --> 00:41:39.130
If you don't want to know, fine.

00:41:40.190 --> 00:41:41.120
W-Wait a minute.

00:41:43.480 --> 00:41:45.670
I know about the acquisition.

00:41:46.670 --> 00:41:47.710
Tell me about it.

00:41:48.150 --> 00:41:50.480
Let's see if your information is correct.

00:41:53.360 --> 00:41:53.920
Come.

00:41:54.150 --> 00:41:54.800
Come here.

00:41:59.420 --> 00:42:02.450
You saw that guy up there just now?

00:42:02.920 --> 00:42:03.880
That is Yu.

00:42:04.510 --> 00:42:06.510
He is competing with Xia Lei

00:42:06.510 --> 00:42:07.800
to acquire this plant.

00:42:08.030 --> 00:42:09.710
I don't care about who he is.

00:42:09.840 --> 00:42:12.230
Xia Lei will win against
anyone competing with him.

00:42:12.230 --> 00:42:13.920
If the plant
falls into the hands of people like you,

00:42:13.920 --> 00:42:14.800
nothing good will come of it.

00:42:14.800 --> 00:42:16.590
Let me tell you, you're wrong about that.

00:42:16.590 --> 00:42:18.120
Can Xia Lei save this plant?

00:42:18.320 --> 00:42:21.000
Can he? He just runs a trading company.

00:42:21.000 --> 00:42:23.530
Once he resells it,
there'll be nothing left.

00:42:24.190 --> 00:42:26.190
You have no idea how powerful Yu is.

00:42:27.280 --> 00:42:29.960
Yu has real money.

00:42:30.590 --> 00:42:31.650
Do you understand?

00:42:33.110 --> 00:42:34.480
If it's really as good as you say,

00:42:34.480 --> 00:42:36.000
why didn't Mr. Song sell the plant

00:42:36.000 --> 00:42:37.280
directly to you guys.

00:42:37.440 --> 00:42:39.760
Why would you be here yapping at me?

00:42:39.760 --> 00:42:41.890
Let me tell you, you're really stupid.

00:42:42.480 --> 00:42:44.150
Why do you think they're stalling?

00:42:44.150 --> 00:42:45.400
Mr. Song is stalling

00:42:45.760 --> 00:42:48.280
to show his competence to his superiors.

00:42:48.880 --> 00:42:51.110
What does Xia Lei
holding out have to do with you?

00:42:51.110 --> 00:42:53.440
Don't try to
drive a wedge between us here.

00:42:53.800 --> 00:42:54.480
We all know that

00:42:54.480 --> 00:42:57.070
Mr. Song's goal is to save the plant.

00:42:57.450 --> 00:42:59.250
Xia Lei is a child from our plant.

00:42:59.280 --> 00:43:00.510
Maybe our Factory No. 3

00:43:00.510 --> 00:43:02.070
will be saved

00:43:02.150 --> 00:43:03.710
and start making a profit.

00:43:03.710 --> 00:43:05.000
You'll be green with envy then.